Note:
RISC-V 32-bit Linux Syscall ABI

This file implements Linux RISC-V 32-bit (ilp32) system calls for the Runa compiler.
The syscall numbering follows the Linux asm-generic table (the same table
linux_arm64 uses); RISC-V does NOT use x86_64's numbering.

Platform-specific details:
- Platform: Linux RISC-V 32-bit
- Syscall mechanism: ecall instruction
- Syscall number register: a7
- Argument registers: a0-a5 (up to 6 arguments)
- Return value: a0
- Error indication: a0 contains errno (negative on error)

Linux RISC-V 32-bit syscall convention:
- a7 = syscall number
- a0-a5 = arguments 1-6
- Stack = arguments 7+ (if needed)
- ecall instruction triggers kernel
- a0 = return value (or errno if negative)

RISC-V 32-bit syscall numbers are the same as RISC-V 64-bit.
This file provides both syscall number constants and wrapper functions.

Dependencies: None (uses inline assembly for syscalls)
:End Note

Note:
============================================================================
SYSCALL NUMBER CONSTANTS
============================================================================
:End Note

